id6672566.page:
Remote Content


To add images or videos to your page in CoLE, click on Edit Page, look for the Insert menu, click on the drop-down arrow, scroll down, and select Remote Content.


URL Field -- Paste the URL of the video that you want to display.

Advanced Settings -- Allows the user to establish the width and height of the display, either as a percentage or in pixels.  The default settings are 100% for the width and 200 px for the height.  For video, the optimal display is represented as a proportion (4:3), such as 640 x 480.


Save -- Click on "Save" to keep the URL and the settings that you have established.

id8807471.page:
Google Maps


To add a Google Map to your page in CoLE, click on Edit Page, look for the Insert menu, click on the drop-down arrow, scroll down, and select Google Maps. 


The default location is Cambridge, England (as shown below).  To change the location, simply enter the zip code or a full address.  For locations in other countries, add a comma followed by the country.

id661559.page:
Calendar


To insert a Calendar on a page in CoLE:

  • Start by clicking on "Edit Page", which reveals the Insert button.
  • Click on the down-arrow to access the menu of options.


  • Click on "Calendar", which will open to the screen below.

  • Do not be alarmed by the widget labeled as "Remote Content".  It contains the Calendar widget.
  • Click on "Save" to save this widget, which then will reveal the screen below, containing the Calendar.

id1338095.page:
Integrated Tools


To access the menu of integrated tools, start by clicking on "Edit Page".  Just below that command, go to "Insert" and click on the down arrow to see the menu of options. Below is the list of options, their purpose, and how to enable them. For assistance, please contact your Instructional Designer (ID).


Remote content

Embeds web pages and videos. Note: a special embed url for YouTube needs to be used.

From my experience, it is best to use this widget to embed content to a page. If you use HTML code to embed a page or video, it is possible that the code may change when you edit the page.

Inserting Images

  • When using the Files and Documents widget, you can insert an image and use advanced settings to resize.
  • Using Chrome or FF: I have found that by using a capture tool, such as SnagIt, I am able to copy and paste an image without the Files and Documents widget and resize using my cursor. Seems to work better on my computer at home than on my computer at work.

RSS feed reader

Features:

  • Add multiple RSS feeds.
  • Sort by source or date.

Settings:

Able to choose feed items and how to display:

Discussion

Features:

  • Add new topic: Shows title of first thread.
  • Reply: use reply or quote.
  • Responses: available by clicking + 4 Replies (under title).
  • Editable by author and instructor.
  • Can not find a delete option.

Comments

Features:

  • Comments only; no reply options.
  • Editable and delete option.

rWiki

Instructionsand feature savailable for use by clicking Edit on toolbar.

id7556870.page:
Assignments


To insert an Assignment on a page in CoLE:

  • Start by clicking on "Edit Page", which reveals the Insert button.
  • Click on the down-arrow to access the menu of options.


  • Click on "Assignments", which will open to the screen below.


  • Do not be alarmed by the widget labeled as "Remote Content".  It contains the Assignments widget.
  • Click on "Save" to save this widget, which then will reveal the screen below, containing the Assignment List.

To add an Assigment, click on "Add", fill in the required fields (marked by asterisks), and complete the remaining optional fields as desired (reflected in the screen below).  When you are done, click on Post (for a final version), Preview (to see how your selections will appear), Draft (to save and work on again later), or Cancel (to delete everything that you have entered).

id8083600.page:
Files and Documents


To insert images and/or documents on a page in CoLE:

  • Start by clicking on "Edit Page", which reveals the Insert button.
  • Click on the down-arrow to access the menu of options.


  • Click on "Files and Documents", which will open to the screen below.


  • Click on "Add New Content", which will open to the screen below.


  • Click on "Browse" and select the file (either an image or a document) from your hard drive.  The title field will automatically populate with the filename of your selection.
  • Add a description and tags, to make it easier to search for the document later.
  • Who Can See It -- The choices are public, logged in users, and only me.  The default setting is public. 
  • Copyright -- The choices are Creative Commons license, copyrighted, no copyright, licensed, and waive copyright.  The default setting is Creative Commons license.
  • Click on "Add" on the right-hand side of the screen.  The default here is the library for the course site.
  • Click on "Done, Add Collected" at the bottom right-hand side of the screen.  NOTE:  If you do not do so, then the file will not be added to your page.
  • The next screen to appear is "Display Settings", as reflected below.


  • Display Style -- Check the box for either original size or thumbnail.  The default setting is full size.
  • Include (optional) -- There are no default settings here.
  • Add Title and Description (optional) -- There are no default settings here.  This option can be useful when you have a list of articles that you want students to read.  For example, add the title of an article to the Title field and the formal citation to the Description field.  When it displays, the Title will automatically appear larger and the citation will follow immediately below.  Also, the entire entry will appear self-contained on the page and separate from other files.
  • Add Selected Content to Page -- Click on this button to save your work here and move to the next page.

  • Save -- Click "Save" on this last page as well.  NOTE: If you do not do so, then the file will not appear on your page.
